Warren Beatty &amp; Faye Dunaway announced the wrong best picture winner, announcing 'La La Land' instead of 'Moonlight'. JOHANNESBURG Warren Beatty and Faye Dunaway announced the wrong best picture winner at the 2017 Oscars.The pair announced that La La Land has won when Moonlight was the actualwinner. Beatty and Dunaway, stars of 1967's Bonnie and Clyde, appeared at the Oscars on Sunday to mark the 50th anniversary of the film.This was Dunaway's first time presenting the best picture award on Oscars night.The La La Land cast and filmmakers took to the stage to accept the award, and then stopped when it became apparent Moonlight had actually won.It was a moment that left the audience gasping with jaws on the ground.</p>WATCH: #ThatAwkwardMoment: Best Picture Mix-up at the Oscars. </p> The moment Moonlight really won at the #Oscars https://t.co/lXHipwu3LR pic.twitter.com/L27UMm8iRV&mdash; The Daily Beast (@thedailybeast) February 27, 2017 </p> It's certainly a moment that Hollywood will be talking about for a long time.Meanwhile, Twitter had a field day with the mishap Steve Harvey in his living room right now pic.twitter.com/gPKdmoqt24 #Oscars&mdash; Shooter McGavin (@ShooterMcGavin_) February 27, 2017 </p> ICYMI #Moonlight actually wins Best Picture. #Oscars pic.twitter.com/rI008Wj90n&mdash; Who What Wear (@WhoWhatWear) February 27, 2017 </p> In a similar blunder, last year, Steve Harvey mistakenly named Miss Colombia as Miss Universe when it was actually Miss Philippines who walked away with the crown.(Edited by Refilwe Pitjeng) WATCH: #ThatAwkwardMoment: Best Picture Mix-up at the Oscars.The moment Moonlight really won at the #Oscars https://t.co/lXHipwu3LR pic.twitter.com/L27UMm8iRVIt's certainly a moment that Hollywood will be talking about for a long time.Meanwhile, Twitter had a field day with the mishap Steve Harvey in his living room right now pic.twitter.com/gPKdmoqt24 #OscarsICYMI #Moonlight actually wins Best Picture. #Oscars pic.twitter.com/rI008Wj90nI